From d840814889bc31ea397b952980191fff43e3e66a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 15:22:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: repair build, remove fabricated claims, honest
 pre-launch repositioning

Build fixes:
- Implement app/dashboard/page.tsx (was empty, broke type check) as a
  clearly-labeled simulated product preview
- Extract inline onSubmit form from server component into a proper
  ContactForm client component (was a prerender crash on Vercel)
- Remove Clerk entirely: placeholder publishable key threw at prerender
  and middleware.ts referenced in README never existed
- Switch next/font/google to bundled geist package: no build-time
  network fetch, CI/Vercel-robust
- Prune 14 unused dependencies (Clerk, Supabase, Radix, RHF, Zod, etc.)
- Fix Chatbot SSR hydration mismatch (impure Date calls during render)
- Fix &amp; rendered literally inside JSX string literals on /solutions
- Add metadataBase; site now builds green with zero env vars

Honesty remediation (legal exposure removed):
- Remove fake customer logos naming real companies (Tridel, EllisDon,
  PCL, Aecon, Mattamy, Minto, Sunnybrook) and fabricated executive
  testimonials attributed to them
- Remove invented metrics: '142 projects', '1,200+ deployments',
  'proven on 200+ job sites', '47 more builders', fake case studies
- Reposition entire site as pre-launch 2026 GTA pilot recruitment;
  all performance numbers labeled engineering targets, all pricing
  labeled target pricing
- Rewrite chatbot with honest scripted answers; ROI calculator
  relabeled as a model with published methodology on /resources
- Replace 9 dead social links with real contact email; prune all
  dead footer/nav links incl. nonexistent dryforge.ai/floorforge.ai
- Add real /legal/privacy (PIPEDA) and /legal/terms pages with
  pre-launch and ROI-model disclaimers
- Contact form: Formspree via NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSPREE_ID with mailto
  fallback; realistic response-time promise
